 {"id":"franken_networkx-e90h","title":"parity: subgraph should preserve live graph attribute updates across graph classes","description":"Graph-family subgraph() currently snapshots the graph attribute dict. After H = G.subgraph([...]), updating G.graph['mode'] from 'orig' to 'updated' is visible through NetworkX subgraph views but FrankenNetworkX still reports the stale original value. Match the upstream live graph-attribute view contract across Graph, DiGraph, MultiGraph, and MultiDiGraph.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T07:56:40.596989489Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T07:56:40.596989489Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-e9dd","title":"fnx-python preserve-mode library tests fail in algorithms test cluster","description":"`rch exec -- cargo test -p fnx-python --lib -- --nocapture` currently fails in `algorithms::tests::{multigraph_projections_preserve_mode,multidigraph_projections_preserve_mode,spanning_helpers_preserve_mode,python_algorithm_wrappers_preserve_mode}`. The failing assertions compare runtime policy decision ledgers and appear unrelated to the Pajek/NodeView.get fix in `franken_networkx-dl59`, but the failures block a clean crate-wide `fnx-python` lib test run and should be triaged separately.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-16T22:11:19.581990262Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-16T22:24:06.268907638Z","closed_at":"2026-04-16T22:24:06.266061279Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
